*CRISPR is in fact not the molecule used to genetically modify organisms*

CRISPR _(or Clustered Regularly Interspaced Short Palindromic Repeats)_ is a part of the genome of some bacteria and cells. CAS9 is the protein/molecule that edits other parts of the genome with information from the CRISPR section.
